The paper deals with the computational complexity of two puzzles involving block pushing, which are problems that fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The puzzles also involve the manipulation of data structures (unit square blocks on an integer lattice), which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). The puzzles require the use of algorithms to find solutions, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The puzzles involve geometric constraints and movements, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the puzzles involve planning and optimization, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
